race.description: Kyneton Horse Of The Year Win Elegance Mdn Plt
race.comment: CAFFETTIERA (14) jumped out well and was narrowly beaten on debut over 1140m at Geelong. Has the inside barrier today and is sure to keep improving for a top metro yard. PATH TO PROFIT (13) is in the premier stable and brings near misses from Bairnsdale and Sandown-Hillside. That's also good form and John Allen replaces the 3kg apprentice. A live chance as well. UYUNI (12) showed enough here on debut to suggest she's a chance. She was expected to need the outing and is sure to have come on. RUSSIAN SKY (8) debuts and won a Camperdown jump-out in August. Profiles well and expected to measure up.
